The governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Bauchi State, Air Marshal Saddique Baba Abubakar (rtd), has cautioned youths against thuggery during the February 25 and March 11 general elections in the state. Sadique spoke yesterday in Bauchi during the inauguration of monitors from LOBITO Group 4 Asiwaju, one of the major support groups for the APC presidential candidate. He assured the youths  that the APC would win the presidential, governorship and other elections without engaging in any act of lawlessness. He said Tinubu is the best man to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari and advised members of the group to mobilise others who are yet to collect their PVCs to do so. Bola Tinubu’s renewed hope (II) Elections will hold in S’East as scheduled – Military The chairman of the steering committee of the group in Bauchi State, Alhaji Idris Lanzai, expressed their determination to work assiduously for APC’s victory in the elections.